  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "source": [
    "### Q2.1\n",
    "\n",
    "1. 70:30 train-test split\n",
    "2. fit a linear regression model using \"Molecular Weight\"\n",
    "3. Provide the slope and intercept of the fitted linear regression model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# get data we need\n",
    "log_solubility = df.iloc[:][\"ESOL predicted log solubility in mols per litre\"].values\n",
    "\n",
    "# prepare X and y\n",
    "X = molecular_weight.reshape(-1,1)\n",
    "y = log_solubility"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "\n",
    "# do 70:30 train:test split\n",
    "test_size = int(len(X)*0.3)\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=test_size, shuffle=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",

      "Slope: [-0.01089703]\n",
      "Intercept: -0.7664045143017582\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
    "\n",
    "# fit the model using training data\n",
    "regressor = LinearRegression().fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "# print slope and intercept\n",
    "print(\"Slope:\", regressor.coef_)\n",
    "print(\"Intercept:\", regressor.intercept_)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Q2.2\n",
    "\n",
    "Report the mean squared error (MSE) for both the training and test sets."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,

   "outputs": [

     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, r2_score\n",

    "y_pred_test = regressor.predict(X_test)\n",
    "print(f\"MSE of test: {mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred_test):.2f}\")"
